dcterms:description: Wikidata is a free, open-source knowledge base that acts as knowledge storage for the structured data of sister Wikimedia projects such as Wikipedia, Wikivoyage, and others. It contains a vast number of entities and relationships stored as facts or triples.
dcterms:title: Wikidata

dcterms:description: A dataset created by the authors from Wikidata that focuses on 13 different demographics, ensuring representation from various continents.
dcterms:title: Demography dataset (specific to 13 demographics)

dcterms:description: TransE is a knowledge graph embedding algorithm that uses translational models to represent entities and relations in a low-dimensional space.
dcterms:title: TransE

dcterms:description: ComplEx is a knowledge graph embedding algorithm that relies on tensor decomposition methods to represent entities and relations as complex vectors.
dcterms:title: ComplEx

dcterms:description: DistMult is another knowledge graph embedding algorithm that uses a bilinear model to represent entities and relations.
dcterms:title: DistMult

dcterms:description: A dataset derived from the analysis of Wikidata focusing on gender-biased occupations.
dcterms:title: Gender-biased occupations

dcterms:title: Male and female-biased occupations (ranked lists)
